                <h2 data-uuid="8d7da9f87e7b4a9c89f00f36b531dcc3"> Document-Based Investigation</h2>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="de64c9916e084497a05a71ea0cc233ac">Part 2: Write a Presentation</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="4170a9592be745e18bdd7fd07c4909b4">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="abe23601ce8540a4bc73fff42608e00a">After the War of 1812, Americans were filled with
                national pride and confidence in the future. U.S. officials asserted a stronger
                foreign policy and a spirit of optimism swept the nation.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="bc2246ecb51142e6a48dac4361f308e6">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="058b371696c94af394b563bf4d1c0daf">How did a rising tide of national pride change the
                United States in the early 1800s? Write a presentation describing the
                impact of nationalism on the United States in the early 1800s. Be sure to tell
                how nationalism affected foreign policy, domestic policy, and American culture.</p>
            <p data-uuid="643509f241d547918b79d0f0cfb783fc">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="8ddc1c3d196446eca292368c2a3bc1fa">
                <li data-uuid="e148261d2f544bbab57dfa2e6ff22183">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="4c94ff15a35a48ce9979be2bf61445eb">
                    Use at least <i>two</i>
                    of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic by citing relevant, well-chosen text
                    or visual evidence&#160;from each document.</li>
                <li data-uuid="89a33224d1864952b68b88c01892074f">Plan your presentation so that it includes an introduction,
                    several body paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph that sums up your ideas and supports the your main points.&#160;</li>
                <li data-uuid="c92f5ce584284cc394c48275a39cf574">Develop your topic with well-chosen facts, details, and examples.&#160;</li>
                <li data-uuid="daaa655329454be5bedfcf3432cf805d">Present
                    information logically and concisely so that an audience can easily identify your key points.&#160;</li>
                <li data-uuid="d49b2814c44b48279e70cdf1c58119ce">&#160;Use technology, such as the Internet or a presentation program, to write and publish your presentation.&#160;&#160;</li>
                <li data-uuid="0c4969dd6327446ca1dd39e79dba4b7e">Include images and other media to illustrate your major points and connect ideas.&#160;</li>
                <li data-uuid="4ab84dee383a436fa1339dac3d746f09">Practice delivering your presentation, using appropriate eye contact and speaking loudly and clearly enough to be heard by an audience.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
            <p data-uuid="ab8acd21b1614aea8ec413fbca83a828"><br />
            </p>
        </section>
